.TH "ssam_controller_suspend" 9 "ssam_controller_suspend" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ssam_controller_suspend \- Suspend the controller.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ssam_controller_suspend
.BI "(struct ssam_controller *ctrl "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctrl" 12
The controller to suspend.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Marks the controller as suspended. Note that display-off and D0-exit
notifications have to be sent manually before transitioning the controller
into the suspended state via this function.

See \fBssam_controller_resume\fP for the corresponding resume function.
.SH "RETURN"
Returns -EINVAL if the controller is currently not in the
"started" state.
